        "This is a study of a single planet, so the results may not be representative of all rocky planets orbiting small stars."
    ],
    "glossary": [
        {
            "term": "Phase Curve",
            "definition": "The change in brightness of a planet as it orbits its star. This allows scientists to map the planet's temperature and look for signs of an atmosphere."
        },
        {
            "term": "Heat Transport Efficiency",
            "definition": "A measure of how efficiently heat is moved from the hot dayside to the cold nightside of a tidally locked planet. A value greater than zero suggests the presence of an atmosphere."
        },
        {
            "term": "Tidally Locked",
            "definition": "When a planet's rotation period is the same as its orbital period, meaning the same side of the planet always faces its star."
        },
        {
            "term": "JWST MIRI",
            "definition": "The Mid-Infrared Instrument on the James Webb Space Telescope, which is used to observe the heat emitted by celestial objects."
        },
